      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      2.0 out of 5 stars Changed formula or fake? No bueno either way
      Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2020
      Have been using ON creatine for many years with great results. Noticed the product in my most recent container had a different consistency than it normally does. Didn't give it too much thought as that often happens with powdered supplements. However, fast forward about 3 weeks and my muscles just felt flatter, with less of a pump when working out. My diet is very consistent and nothing else had changed with exercise or sleeping habits either. Checked the label and compared it to a previous container. It now says PACKAGED in the USA - previously said MANUFACTURED in the USA. The previous label also clearly noted it was Creapure creatine, the new label makes no mention of that anywhere on the label. Looks like I will be going elsewhere for my creatine in the future.UPDATE: After some digging, it appears that ON has confirmed that their creatine no longer uses Creapure. So it's definitely their new formula and probably not a fake. I'd say that just puts it on par with all the other marginal creatine on the market, manufactured wherever it's the cheapest.

      5.0 out of 5 stars How to dissolve quickly.
      Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2018
      Size: 120 Servings (Pack of 1)Verified Purchase
      Creatine is a fantastic supplement, even if you are not a body builder. Btw, Creatine has a half-life of 6-8 weeks in the body.

      Some users might have digestive issues if it is not dissolved. Any easy way to resolve this is to put about 4 oz of hot water in your cup or blender bottle and then add the creatine. Stir for a couple minutes and it should be completely or sufficiently dissolved. Add some cold water (I add Spring Water with a couple ice cubes). I then add my Whey Protein Powder and shake my blender bottle.

      Adding the hot water may be a slight inconvience but is worth it. Think of it as "pre-digestion".

      Stephen Patrick
      5.0 out of 5 stars Remember kids, Creatine Monohydrate isn't completely water soluble!
      Reviewed in the United States on May 19, 2022
      Size: 120 Servings (Pack of 1)Verified Purchase
      I've been using this product for months now while I attempt to get the rest of my weight off of me. I used to be 320 pounds and lost 100 unaided by supplements. I did it all through intensive exercise and a caloric deficit. When I officially hit 100 pounds lost in December of 2021, I decided to grab some creatine to aid in keeping the muscle I already had while I tried to get the rest of the fat off of my body (along with 1 to 1.2 grams of protein per pound of bodyweight and keeping my other macros in check). This stuff has been amazing. Not only have I continued to lose weight through my caloric deficit and intensive weightlifting regime, but I have also kept a majority of my muscle and have GAINED a substantial amount of muscle as well! At the time of writing this review (5/19/2022), I have lost over 130 pounds and am sitting right around 188 pounds.

      This is not a miracle substance. You have to put work in at the gym to see gains and religiously take 5g a day (I just mix it in my pre-workout). I don't believe in a loading phase because of the research that I have followed so I just started taking 5g and have been for 5 months now. This has helped me so much in getting the fat off of my body while cutting, keeping the muscle I already had, and gaining a LOT of new muscle. I am incredibly happy and will continue using this for the foreseeable future.

      Last little thing, I've been seeing a lot of 1-star reviews for this saying things like "does not dissolve in water" and "like drinking sand". You must understand that Creatine Monohydrate has incredibly poor water solubility and will not dissolve at all in cold water. The only advice I have for you is to man up and just drink it (or woman up! and or non-binary up! You got this!). You WILL see results, but you must take it religiously and you must consistently push yourself in the gym along with keeping your diet in check. Overall, I love this creatine and will be continuing to take it. It's been an amazing help and has boosted my confidence.
